1.JOB
  a.Whenever a new coroutine is launched, it will return a job.
    a.1.  it can be used to wait for the coroutine to do some work.... join() method
    a.2.  it can be used to cancel the coroutine..... cancel() method

 b.
withTimeOut()......TIME CONCEPT
isActive.......CHECKS IS COROUTINE JOB IS CANCELLED
cancel() Method
join() Method



 ****************  DEFINITION **************************

 A Job is a cancellable thing with a life-cycle that culminates in its completion.
  job is created with launch coroutine builder. It runs a specified block of code and completes on
  completion of this block.

 ****************  DEFINITION **************************
